==English==

===Etymology===

From Greek diglōttis ''δίγλωττις'', from di- ''δί'' ("two") and -glōttis ''γλωττίς'' (a tongue-shaped mouthpiece in a flute, etc.), from glōtta ''γλῶττα'', secondary form of glōssa ''[[γλῶσσα]]'' ("tongue", "language").

